    "locales": {
      "en": {
        "name": "AMT Hardballer Longslide .45 ACP pistol",
        "shortName": "AMT",
        "description": "AMT Hardballer are a series of pistols that are part of the 1911 platform (based on the .45 ACP M1911) made by Arcadia Machine & Tool (AMT) from 1977 to 2002. The Hardballer was the first entirely stainless steel 1911 pattern pistol. Other features included adjustable rear sights and a lengthened grip safety. The pistol was notably featured in a variety of media including Hitman and Terminator."
      }
